


what .js-lang can do on HTML-page in browser ?


 using browser provided APIs, can bring any dynamic activity to web-page

 browser APIs , e.g DOM, XHR , Timer , HTML-5 APIs ...  

  ==> implemented based on w3c standards and abstracted as .js objects & func


using DOM 
------------
  -> can create,retreive,update,delement HTML elements
  -> can change element's style
  -> can change element's attributes
  -> can change element's text or inner-content
  -> can listen events on eleemnts
  -> can create rich-UI components

using XHR
----------
  --> can communicate with server async, update results in existing page

using Timer-API
---------------
  setTimeout(),setInterval()


HTML-5 APIs
---------------  

ref : https://developer.mozilla.org/en/docs/Web/Guide/HTML/HTML5

  1. connectivity

     a. Web Sockets
     b. Server-Sent-Events

  2. Storage API

     a. sessionStaorage
     b. localStorage
     c. indexedDB

  3. MultiMedia

     a. Audio/Video support
     b. Camera API

  4. Graphics and Effects 

     a. Canvas API ==> to draw shape/text/images
     b. SVG
     c. WebGL

  5. Performance & Integration 

     a. Web-Worker
     b. XHR-level2
     c. History API
     d. Drag and Drop


  6. Device Access

    a. Geo 

  7. Styling

    

ref : http://caniuse.com/


--------------------------------------------------------------------

 plain-js  : limitations


 --> too much code for simple operation
 --> browser compatibility  ( main issue )
 --> performance  ( e.g DOM manipulation)

      DOM -> selection,insertion,updation shud me minimal

 --> memory leaks

     --> cleaning unwanted DOM elements
     --> removing event-listers , before DOM element destroy..

--> code organization is difficult

     Model
     View
     Controller ( logig to change Model)

--> good patterns & best practices...

